subs.text: I did some searches on Tina Weymouth, the bass player for the Talking Heads. In an interview with her husband, he said everyone's eyes were on her when they performed, I thought I was the only one. When I listen to a Talking Heads song with a strong beat (a lot of them) I think of her. That's what she represents, the driving power of the group is a woman. Try listening to this song and look at images of her.
Tina Weymouth, bass player for Talking Heads.
